games.comment: Colin Kaepernick, who rushed for 50 yards and a touchdown on 5 attempts.

Colin Kaepernick led his team down the field, completing his first 8 passes for 115 yards. This has been a theme for Kaepernick this season. He'd start quickly and then get bogged down completely for 2 quarters before making a last-ditch effort to come back. Last week, that worked for the 49ers' second win of the season against the Rams, which happened to be the 49ers' second win against any team.
